=== Evolving Planet === * Evolving Planet follows the evolution of life on Earth over 4 billion years. The exhibit showcases fossils of [[Single celled organisms|single-celled organisms]], [[Permian]] [[Synapsid|snapsids]], [[dinosaur]]s, extinct mammals, and early [[Hominidae|hominoids]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.fieldmuseum.org/at-the-field/exhibitions/evolving-planet|title=Evolving Planet|last=jhoog|date=2010-11-11|work=The Field Museum|access-date=2018-03-31|language=en}}</ref> {| class="wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" !Species represented in Evolving Planet !Type !Specimen Notes ! |- |''[[Tiktaalik]]'' |[[Sarcopterygii|sarcopterygian]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Tiktaalik Chicago.JPG|frameless]] |- |''[[Acheloma]]'' |[[temnospondyl]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Acheloma cumminsi.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Bradysaurus]]'' |[[pareiasaur]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:FMNH Bradysaurus.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Cacops]]'' |[[dissorophid]] [[temnospondyls]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Cacops Field Museum.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Captorhinus]]'' |[[Captorhinidae|captorhinid]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:FMNH Captorhinus.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Dicynodont]]'' |[[anomodont]] [[therapsid]]s |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Aulacephalodon peavoti.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Edaphosaurus]]'' |[[Edaphosauridae|edaphosaurid]] [[synapsid]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Edaphosaurus.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Eryops]]'' |[[temnospondyl]]s |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:FMNH Eryops.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Labidosaurus]]'' |[[anapsid]] [[reptile]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:FMNH Labidosaurus.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Ophiacodon]]'' |[[ophiacodontidae]] [[synapsid]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:Ophiacodon mirus fm.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Seymouria]]'' |primitive [[tetrapod]] |[[fossil]] [[skeleton]] |[[File:FMNH Seymouria.jpg|frameless]] |- |''[[Anchiceratops]]'' |[[Ceratopsidae|ceratopsid]] [[dinosaur]] |[[fossil]] [[skull]] |[[Fi