[[File:First National Congress of Science Fiction.jpg|thumb|right|Newspaper article, February 1974]] '''Jean Sendy''' (1910–1978)<ref>[http://mysteretboulesdecristal.centerblog.net/6458994-jean-sendy-1910-1978 Mystère et boules de cristal]</ref> was a [[French people|French]] writer and translator, author of works on [[esotericism|esoterica]] and [[UFO]] phenomena. He was also an early proponent of the [[ancient astronaut]] hypothesis.<ref>[http://raelian.com/en/jean_sendy.php Profile for Jean Sendy]</ref>
==Ancient astronauts== He wrote the 1968 book ''The moon: The key to the Bible'' in which he claimed the word "Elohim" mentioned in the Hebrew [[Book of Genesis|Genesis]] of the Bible, which is usually translated as [[God]], should in fact be translated in the plural as "Gods" because the singular of the word ''Elohim'' is ''Eloah''.<ref>Jean Sendy, La Lune, Cle de la Bible, 1968 pg. 7</ref> He claimed that the "Gods" were actually space travelers (an [[Extraterrestrial life|alien]] race of [[humanoids]]). Sendy believed that Genesis was factual history of ancient astronauts colonizing earth who became "angels in human memory". The book contains similar ideas to that of the UFO religion [[Raëlism]].<ref>Susan J. Palmer, Aliens adored: Raël's UFO religion, 2004, p. 28</ref><ref>Diana G. Tumminia, Alien worlds: social and religious dimensions of extraterrestrial contact, 2007 p. 65 {{ISBN|978-0-8156-0858-5}}</ref><ref>[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=fr&u=http://www.prevensectes.com/rael19.htm&ei=EIbeTZiLOYG2hAedwIHDCg&sa=X&oi=translate&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ7gEwAA&prev=/search%3Fq%3Dwww.prevensectes.com%2Bjean%2Bsendy%26hl%3Den%26safe%3Doff%26biw%3D1345%26bih%3D627%26prmd%3Divnso Jean Sendy and Raëlism]</ref>
In his 1969 book ''Those Gods who made Heaven and Earth'', Sendy claimed that space travelers 23,500 years ago arrived in the [[solar system]] in a large hollow sphere and seeded humanity.
