'''Kalmyk Americans'''<ref>[http://www.kalmykamericansociety.org/ Kalmyk American Society. February 4, 2007]{{Verify credibility|failed=y|date=October 2012}}</ref> are [[Americans]] of [[Kalmyk people|Kalmyk descent]]. These people originated in [[Dzungaria]] (located in contemporary China), but moved to [[Russia]] in the 16th century where they were assimilated. In 2000, their number in [[New Jersey]] numbered about 3,000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.njdigitalhighway.org/kalmyks_stud.php |title=Kalmyk |last1=Sanderson |first1=Sagan T. |work=''"The Encyclopedia of New Jersey"'', Rutgers University Press |publisher=[[New Jersey Digital Highway]] |accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref>
